It was a fun activity and the memorization was a bit difficult for me.
THE BOY BELIEVED THAT HE WAS RICH, BUT IN FACT HE WAS NOT.
HIS FATHER HAD BEEN OFFERED A POSITION AS A CUSTODIAN FOR A LIBARAY.
THE FATHER WORKED HARD IN THAT LIBRARY AND EVEN WOULD WAX THE TOP OF THE SHELVES.
WAXING THE TOP OF THE SHELVES WOULD MAKE THE LIBARY SHELFS SHINE AS YOU WENT UP THE STAIRS IN THE LIBARAY.
THE BOY STATED THAT DURING THE DAY, HE HAD TO KEEP QUIET, BUT DURING THE NIGHT HE COULD RUN AROUND AND BE AS LOUD AS HE WANTED.
HE MENTIONED THAT DURING CERTAIN LATE NIGHTS, 3AM, HE COULD GO IN AND READ AS MANY BOOKS.
HE WAS THE FIRST IN HIS FAMILY TO GRADUATE HIGH SCHOOL AND GRADUATE FROM A UNIVERSIT.
WHEN HE TOOK HIS FATHER TO SEE HIS OFFICE WITH HIS NAME ON THE DOOR, HIS FATHER JUST LOOKED AT IT WITH HAPPINESS.
EVEN THOUGH HIS REACTION WAS NOT VERY EXPRESSIONAL, THE SON COULD SEE THAT HIS FATHER WAS PROUD.
HE GIVES THANKS TO HIS FATHER BEING A CUSTODIAN.
THIS ALLOWED HIM TO ENJOY READING AND CONTINUE HIS MOTIVATION WITH HIS EDUCATION.
THE BOY BELIEVED HE WAS RICH, BUT HIS PARENTS ASSURED HIM THAT HE WAS NOT.
HIS FATHER WAS OFFERED A CUSTODIAN POSITION THAT HE TOOK.
THIS POSITION ALLOWED HIS SON TO BE IN THE LIBRARY AND READ AS MANY BOOKS AS HE WANTED.
THE BOYS FAVORITE HOBBY WAS TO READ BECAUSE OF THE AVABILITY OF UNLIMITED BOOKS HE HAD AT THE LIBRARY.
HE WOULD STAY AT TIMES UNTIL 3AM AND READ, WHILE HIS FATHER WAS DOING HIS WORK.
HIS FATHER TOOK PRIDE IN HIS WORK AND EVEN WAXED THE TOP OF THE SHELVES.
THE WAXED SHELVES COULD BE SEEN AS AN INDIVIDUAL WAS GOING UP STAIRS IN THE BUILDING.
THE SON WAS THE FIRST IN HIS FAMILY TO GRADUATE HIGH SCHOOL AND THE FIRST TO GRADUATE COLLEGE.
ALL PRIOR FAMILY MEMBERS ONLY ACHIEVED BELOW A HIGH SCHOOL DIPLOMA.
WHEN THE SON BECAME A PROFESSIONAL AS A PROFESSOR, HE TOOK HIS FATHER TO SEE THE DOOR WITH HIS NAME ON IT.
HIS FATHER DID NOT REACT WITH EMOTIONS, BUT HE WAS HAPPY TO SEE HIS SON BECOME SOMEONE.
